  "prompt": "Is romantic love real love?",
  "response": "Romantic love is often considered a real and significant form of love, but its validity and depth can vary from person to person. It typically encompasses strong emotional and physical attraction, intimacy, and passion, and it can lead to deep connections and commitments between individuals. \n\nHowever, some people argue that romantic love can be fleeting or influenced by cultural and social factors, while others believe it can coexist with other forms of love, such as companionship or familial love. Ultimately, whether romantic love is seen as \"real\" love often depends on individual beliefs and experiences. It can be profound and meaningful for many people, while for others, it may not encompass the full spectrum of what love can entail.",
